<item>
            <title>[SOLR-2536] add reloadCache feature to ExternalFileField</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2536</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;spin off from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1607&quot; title=&quot;use a proper key other than IndexReader for ExternalFileField and QueryElevationCompenent to work properly when reopenReaders is set to true&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1607&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1607&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. To fix ExternalFileField bug described &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1607&quot; title=&quot;use a proper key other than IndexReader for ExternalFileField and QueryElevationCompenent to work properly when reopenReaders is set to true&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1607&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1607&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I&apos;d propose introducing reloadCache feature over using proper key other than IndexReader.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
